ubinstein\n   |title=Taiwan A New History|place=New York|publisher=M.E. Sharpe, Inc\n   |isbn=9781563248160\n}}.\n* {{citation\n   |last=Teng\n   |first=Emma Jinhua\n   |year=2004\n   |title=Taiwan's Imagined Geography:Chinese Travel Writing and Pictures 1683-1895\n   |publisher=The Harvard University Asia Center |location = MA |isbn=978-0-674-01451-0\n}}.\n* {{citation\n   |last=Wachman\n   |first=Alan M.\n   |author-link1= Alan M. Wachman\n   |year=1994\n   |title=Taiwan: National Identity and Democratization\n   |publisher=M.E. Sharpe |location = New York\n}}.\n* {{citation\n   |last=Wilson\n   |first=Richard W\n   |year=1970\n   |title=The Political Socialization of Children in Taiwan\n   |publisher=M.I.T. Press |location = Cambridge, MA\n}}.\n* {{citation\n   |last=Wolf | first=Arthur\n   |last2=Huang | first2=Chieh-shan\n   |year=1980\n   |title=Marriage and Adoption in China\n   |place=Stanford, CA|publisher=Stanford University Press\n}}.\n* {{citation\n   |last=Wu\n   |first=David Y.H\n   |year=2002\n   |chapter=The Construction of Chinese and Non-Chinese Identities\n   |editor=Susan D. Blum |editor2=Lionel M. Jenson\n   |title=China Off Center: Mapping the Margins of the Middle Kingdom\n   |publisher=University of Hawaii Press |location = HA\n}}.\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|People of Taiwan}}\n<!-- These links need to be worked into the article -->\n* [https://2009-2017.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/35855.htm Taiwan], Bureau of East Asian and Pacific Affairs, U.S. Department of State\n\n{{Taiwan related articles}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taiwanese People}}\n[[Category:Taiwanese people| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Dispute about|the romanisation scheme for words in the Hokkien language|date=December 2019}}{{Infobox ethnic group\n| group = Taiwanese people{{efn native lang|tw|name=word1\n  |t=\u81fa\u7063\u4eba\n  |p=T\u00e1iw\u0101n-r\u00e9n\n  |m=T\u00e2i-o\u00e2n-l\u00e2ng\n  |s=Th\u00f2i-v\u00e0n-ng\u00ecn\n  |ma=D\u00e0i-u\u0103ng-n\u00e8\u0324ng}}