ala|first=A. J.|title=Adarsha Sadhu: An Ideal Monk |date=1934|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-62386-6|edition=First paperback edition, 2014|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ilFkAgAAQBAJ}}\n* {{citation|last=Taliaferro|last2=Marty|title=A dictionary of philosophy of Religion|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=78962vlrCDcC|date=2010|isbn=978-1-4411-1197-5}}\n* {{citation |last=Tandon |first=Om Prakash  |title=Jaina Shrines in India |publisher=Publications Division, [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting (India)|Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]], [[Government of India]] |isbn=978-81-230-1013-7 |date=2002 |origyear=1968 |edition=1 |location=[[New Delhi]] }}\n* {{citation |last=Taylor |first=Bron |authorlink=Bron Taylor |title=Encyclopedia of Religion and Nature |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i4mvAwAAQBAJ |year=2008 |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic |isbn=978-1-4411-2278-0}}\n* {{citation |last=Titze |first=Kurt |authorlink= |title=Jainism: A Pictorial Guide to the Religion of Non-Violence |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass]] |edition=2 |date=1998 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=loQkEIf8z5wC |isbn=978-81-208-1534-6}}\n* {{citation |last=von Dehsen |first=Christian |title=Philosophers and Religious Leaders |date=13 September 2013 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |isbn=978-81-208-1376-2}}\n* {{citation |last=von Glasenapp |first=Helmuth |authorlink=Helmuth von Glasenapp |title=Jainism: An Indian Religion of Salvation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WzEzXDk0v6sC |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass]] (Reprinted 1999) |date=1925 |location=[[Delhi]] |isbn=978-81-208-1376-2}}\n* {{citation |first=Kristi L. |last=Wiley |title=The A to Z of Jainism |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kUz9o-EKTpwC |date=2009 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=978-0-8108-6821-2}}\n* {{citation |last=Williams |first=George M. |title=Handbook of Hindu Mythology |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N7LOZfwCDpEC |year=2008|publisher=Oxford University Pr