s|2002}} }}\n* {{citation |last=Heehs|first=Peter|authorlink=Peter Heehs|title=Indian Religions: A Historical Reader of Spiritual Expression and Experience|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HTepAfJv_6YC|publisher=C. Hurst & Co. Publishers|date=2002|location=|isbn=978-1-85065-497-1}}\n* {{citation |last=Jacobi |first=Hermann| title= Jaina Sutras (Translation)|editor = Max Muller (The Sacred Books of the East Series, Volume XXII) |url=https://archive.org/stream/jainasutrasparti029233mbp#page/n333/mode/2up |date=1964 | publisher = Motilal Banarsidass (Original: Oxford University Press)}}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Champat Rai|authorlink=Champat Rai Jain |title= The Change of Heart |url=https://archive.org/details/TheChangeOfHeart |date=1939 |quote= |ref={{sfnref|Champat Rai Jain|1939}}}} {{PD-notice}}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Gokulchandra |title=Samantabhadrabh\u0101rat\u012b |date=2015 |publisher=[[Ach\u0101rya Sh\u0101ntis\u0101gar Chani Smriti Granthmala]] |location=[[Budh\u0101n\u0101]], [[Muzaffarnagar]] |isbn=978-81-90468879 |edition=1st |ref={{sfnref|Gokulchandra Jain|2015}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Hiralal |last2=Jain |first2=Dharmachandra |authorlink2=Dharmachandra Jain |title=Jaina Tradition in Indian Thought |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uIHXAAAAMAAJ |date=1 January 2002 |isbn=9788185616841}}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Hiralal |last2=Upadhye |first2=Adinath Neminath |authorlink2=A.N. Upadhye |title=Mahavira, his times and his philosophy of life|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GHfzERhGUjQC |date=2000 |origyear=1974 |publisher=[[Bharatiya Jnanpith]]}}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Jyotindra |last2=Fischer |first2=Eberhard |title=Jaina Iconography |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gFZ7vQ2jwlEC |publisher=BRILL Academic |date=1978 |isbn=978-90-04-05259-8 }}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Kailash Chand |title=Lord Mah\u0101v\u012bra and His Times |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8-TxcO9dfrcC |date=1991 |p